 East London - Three Ward by-elections are happening in the Eastern Cape on Wednesday in three local municipalities. The by-elections are being contested by six candidates from four political parties: The ward was previously represented by the ANC and became vacant as a result of the councillor’s resignation. The voter turnout for this ward in the 2016 Municipal Elections was 58.48% and the ANC candidate won the ward with 62.54% of valid votes. The ward was previously represented by the ANC and became vacant as a result of the councillor’s resignation. The voter turnout for this ward in the 2016 Municipal Elections was 67.25% and the ANC candidate won the ward with 56.08% of valid votes. Note that the voting stations in this ward will close earlier and will be open from 7 am to 7 pm. The ward was previously represented by the ANC and became vacant as a result of the councilor’s death. The voter turnout for this ward in the 2016 Municipal Elections was 53.88% and the ANC candidate won the ward with 73.45% of valid votes. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 